  "title": "QC Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Perform in‑process and final inspection of manufactured parts and assemblies.</li><li>Conduct dimensional and visual checks using appropriate measuring tools (e.g., calipers, micrometers, gauges)</li><li>Ensure all products comply with quality standards, specifications, and customer requirements</li><li>Document inspection results and prepare quality reports.</li><li>Collaborate closely with Production and Engineering teams on quality matters.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirement</strong></p><ul><li>Min NTC / GCE ‘O’ Level / GCE ‘N’ Level</li><li>Entry level candidates are welcome to apply.</li><li>Able to interpret basic mechanical drawing.</li><li>Proficient with Microsoft Excel.</li><li><strong>CMM experience or knowledge</strong> is a strong advantage</li><li>Ability to work independently or as part of a team.</li><li>Able to communicate in simple English.</li><li>5 work day work week with overtime provided</li></ul>",
